# Week 3: Auditing & Network Monitoring

 Final Phase Objective
The goal for the final week was to implement active monitoring and perform a network-level security scan to ensure the application environment is fully visible and protected.

Security Auditing (Winston Logger)
I integrated the `winston` logging library to create an automated security audit trail.
Function:** Logs failed login attempts and critical system errors with high-precision timestamps.
Evidence:** The generated `security.log` file tracks all suspicious activity for later forensic analysis.

Network Reconnaissance (Nmap)
I performed an Nmap scan to map the attack surface of the local environment.
Discovery:** Verified that only Port 3000 is open for the Node.js server.
Outcome:** Confirmed no unnecessary services are exposed, reducing the risk of side-channel attacks.

Internship Conclusion
Over the last three weeks, I have moved this application from a highly vulnerable state to a professional-grade secure system featuring defensive headers, encryption, and active auditing.